goals.question: What is the relationship between income and health?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of income vs health
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a correlation between income and health, and if countries with higher income have better health outcomes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of population across different regions?
goals.visualization: bar chart of population by region
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the population distribution across different regions and identify which regions have the highest and lowest populations.

goals.question: What is the average income by region?
goals.visualization: box plot of income by region
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the income distribution across different regions and identify which regions have the highest and lowest average incomes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of health across different regions?
goals.visualization: box plot of health by region
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the health distribution across different regions and identify which regions have the highest and lowest life expectancies.

goals.question: What is the relationship between income and population?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of income vs population
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a correlation between income and population, and if countries with higher income have larger populations.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='income', y='health', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income and health?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region')['population'].sum().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='population', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['income'] = data['income'].astype(float)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="region", y="income", data=data)
    chart.axhline(data['income'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Income: {:.2f}'.format(data['income'].mean()))
    chart.set_title('What is the average income by region?')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
